  "prompt": "Should I trademark the name of my startup?",
  "response": "Here are some considerations for trademarking your startup's name:\n\nPros of Trademarking:\n1. Legal protection against others using your name\n2. Establishes brand ownership\n3. Can increase company/brand credibility\n4. Prevents potential future legal disputes\n5. Asset value for your business\n\nCons/Considerations:\n1. Cost (filing fees range $250-$350)\n2. Time investment in application process\n3. Not mandatory for all businesses\n4. Only protects name in specific business categories\n\nWhen to seriously consider trademarking:\n- Unique, memorable business name\n- Planning significant growth/expansion\n- Operating in competitive market\n- Developing strong brand identity\n- Potential for national/international presence\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Conduct thorough name search\n2. Check trademark database\n3. Consult intellectual property lawyer\n4. Decide on federal vs. state trademark\n5. File appropriate documentation\n\nUltimately, the decision depends on your specific business goals, budget, and growth strategy. A trademark isn't always necessary but can be valuable protection for your brand.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
